transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra. My name is Jessie. May I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Jeff Highfield.

Speaker 1: Awesome. Mr. Highfield, can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: 74002.

Speaker 1: One moment. Let me locate your account.

Speaker 2: All right. You received your mail at P.O. Box 116 in Barnstall, Oklahoma, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: And you recently got another shipment?

Speaker 1: Yes, I did. I was wondering, because I ordered, the first time I ordered 25 and then they sent me 25 again here.

Speaker 2: I was wondering what the deal is.

Speaker 1: Yeah, what happened?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's fine, but I just wanted to make sure there wasn't a plan where it's going to keep sending them every couple of months.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, let me make sure that you're not on that. I can make sure that this is – you prefer it at will, right?

Speaker 2: Just order whenever you feel like it?

Speaker 1: Yes, yes.

Speaker 2: No problem. Okay, let me do that for you. Let's see here. And you have two options.

Speaker 1: And just so you know, to keep your prescription active as well as your VIP status, you can choose – we can pause this.

Speaker 2: Basically what it means is when we pause it, it becomes at will. You place an order whenever you want to.

Speaker 1: You don't get wacky stuff in the mail and all that fun stuff.

Speaker 2: However, to keep the prescription active, you get one refill at the end of six months if you do not place a refill, right?

Speaker 1: So if you don't get any other refills at the end of six months, you get one refill to keep your prescription active. Okay? Is that all right?

Speaker 2: Well, yeah. I just don't want them to go into waste because right now I'm having trouble with my girlfriend's menopause issues.

Speaker 1: So I'm not getting to take them very often. I don't want them – I think it's been – yeah.

Speaker 2: So I didn't know whether I had to go about it. Yeah.

Speaker 1: Sure. If you want the next refill, I can just reduce it to ten so that way you don't get stockpiled.

Speaker 2: So that way in six months if you don't place an order, you just get ten pills but instead of 25.

Speaker 1: And that way it keeps everything active.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah. That would be fine.

Speaker 1: Okay. Super. All right. We'll do that then. You are all set, sir. Is there anything else I can help you with?

Speaker 2: No. That'll do it. I appreciate your help. Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good day, sir. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye-bye.
